What i love about this game is the battles from a story perspective. When i first started playing, i treated it like i was playing another FF game where the fights werent serious at all and it was just a grind for xp.

In expedition 33, every fight could be your last. Literally on the world map, when you get into your first fight, the music sounds like a boss fight but in reality its just a trash mob. And should your team lose that fight, you're slapped with an Expedition Failed screen. Meaning your team amounted to nothing.

Everything in this game is taken seriously and i have to admit, this little bit (along with the prologue) made me fall in love with this game.

The Paintress is *not* actually responsible for the Gommage. The real Renoir is constantly using his painter powers to try to destroy the canvas (the world) while Aline (the Paintress) is trying to save it. As time goes by he weakens her and she is unable to maintain her oldest creations. It is Renoir that is the cause of the Gommage by limiting her ability to maintain these older creations; the number she paints is a warning to her creations that she will not be able to sustain them anymore when they hit that age.

And for anyone wondering, the reason Nevrons, Gestrals and the other "species" there don't get Gommaged is because they are not her creations; they are the creations of Verso (or the last part of Verso's soul that is still painting within the canvas)... except the Axons, which are the real Renoir's creations.
